This is Notes for Date and cal commands 
----------------------------------------

Date Command
--------------
date command can be used to fetch current local date time from system

1) date 		-> Returns local date and time

Various option for date command is 

2) date +%Y		-> display year in YYYY format
3) date +%y		-> display year in YY format
4) date +%m		-> display month in MM format
5) date +%d		-> display day in DD format
6) date +%H		-> display hour HH value in 24 hour format
7) date +%M		-> display minute MM format
8) date +%S		-> display seconds SS format

we can combine multiple options to create desired format
9) date +%d/%m/%Y	-> display date in DD/MM/YYYY format

Cal Command
--------------
cal command we can use to display calendar

1) cal 			-> display current year calendar
2) cal YYYY		-> display specified year calendar 
3) cal MM YYYY		-> display specific month calendar

